<?php $__env->startSection('content'); ?><p>The Vampire Diaries star Claire Holt gave birth to her second child, with husband Andrew Joblon last week. </p>

<p>And on Saturday, the actress shared a sweet photo of her newborn baby girl Elle to Instagram. </p>

<p>The 32-year-old reflected on motherhood, explaining that it has been a 'different experience' the second time around. </p>

<p>Sweet picture: On Saturday, Vampire Diaries star Claire Holt (pictured) shared a sweet photo of her newborn baby girl Elle (pictured) to Instagram</p>

<p>'It’s been such a different experience this time. I feel so much more relaxed and confident,' she captioned the photo.</p>

<p>'I don’t question every single decision that I make and know that all that matters is that she is loved, fed, and safe.' </p>

<p>She went on to add that her first child James, is the 'sweetest big brother' and he is 'adjusting well' to the new baby. </p>

<p>'I don’t question every single decision that I make and know that all that matters is that she is loved, fed, and safe,' she said</p>

<p>In the photo, Elle was pictured fast asleep on Claire's shoulder following a feed. </p>

<p>Claire and her real estate executive husband welcomed Elle Last week.</p>

<p>The TV star shared the news with her fans on her Instagram page.</p>

